      "shrink",
      "clip"
    ]
  },
  {
    "TITLE":"Monte Carlo steps",
    "INST":"Subtomogram alignment to symmetry axis is done using e2symsearch3d.py. e2symsearch3d.py uses a downhill search using the simplex algorithm to align to symmetry axis. However the downhill search can get stuck in local minima, so a number of random starting positions are investigation. List this number here. Use higher numbers for lower symmtry ",
    "WIDGETS":[
      "steps"
    ]
  },
  {
